  <brief_title>An Observational Study of Avastin (Bevacizumab) in Patients With Metastatic Colorectal Cancer (ACORN)</brief_title>
  <official_title>An Observational Study of AvastinÂ® (Bevacizumab) in Combination With Chemotherapy for Treatment of First-line Metastatic Colorectal Adenocarcinoma</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Hoffmann-La Roche</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Hoffmann-La Roche</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      This prospective, multi-center, observational study will assess the safety and efficacy of
      Avastin (bevacizumab) in daily practice in patients with metastatic colorectal cancer who
      have received no previous treatment for advanced disease and are receiving Avastin in
      combination with a standard of care first-line chemotherapy regimen. Data will be collected
      for 1.5 years or until death.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
